        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-30T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-30T10:00:00-05:00" n="41" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d41">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/4–3046: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Certain <gloss type="to">Diplomatic and Consular Officers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="36" xml:id="d41fn1">At Bangkok, Batavia, London, Moscow, Paris, and
                        Singapore.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-30T11:00:00-04:00">April 30, 1946—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>French in Hanoi fear Chinese attack on French civilians, soldiers, any incident
                    likely become serious citywide fight. Some French believe Chinese planning
                    overrun French, overthrow Vietnam Government, establish Chinese fostered Dong
                    Minh Hoi Party in power then ask Chinese assistance thus allowing Chinese troops
                    remain Indochina. Consul Saigon suggests<note n="37" xml:id="d41fn2">Telegram
                        121, April 27, 1946, 10 a.m., not printed.</note> general order from Chiang
                    Kai-shek might avert incident.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
